\omega _{S}&=&x\left(d\psi +x_1dT\psi +( ix_1+1/2\bar{\psi}\psi ) d\bar{
\theta}\right)\\
\omega _{\bar S}&=&x\left(d\bar{\psi}+x_1dT\bar{\psi}

\omega _{K}&=&x^2\left(dx_1-\frac{i}{2}d\bar{\psi} \psi
+\frac{i}{2}\bar{\psi}d\psi+
x_1^2dT-x_1(d\theta\psi +\bar{\psi}d\bar{\theta})\right)\\
\omega_U& =&\frac{1}{2}\bar{\psi}\psi dT-\frac{i}{2}d\theta \psi +\frac{i}{2}\bar{\psi}d\bar{\theta}
\

\begin{eqnarray}\label{ExpD}
 \omega _{D}&=&
\omega_{H}(xdx/dt-x_1x^2-i\bar{\psi}x Dx+i\psi x\bar{D}x)+\\
&&\omega _{Q}(Dx+x/2\psi
)+\bar{\omega}_{\bar{Q}}(\bar{D}x-x/2\bar{\psi}),\nonumber\\
\omega_S&=&x^2\omega_H(x\dot\psi-ix\bar\psi D\psi+ix\psi\bar D\psi)+\nonumber\\
&&x^2\omega_QD\psi+\omega_{\bar Q}(x^2\bar D \psi+ix_1x^2+1/2x^2\bar\psi\psi).
\

\begin{eqnarray}\label{invariants}
I_{S/\bar Q}=\frac{\omega_S}{\omega_{\bar Q}}&=&  x^2\bar D \psi+ix_1x^2+1/2x^2\bar\psi\psi,        \\
I_{\bar S/Q}=\frac{\omega_{\bar S}}{\omega_{Q}}&=& x^2 D \bar\psi-ix_1x^2+1/2x^2\bar\psi\psi
